@PunkyKubrick That’s a great go to! I usually follow it up with, “if I could, don’t you think I’d be rich af by now?” I have won at gambling multiple times as well as winning contests throughout my life, but only when I feel like I should play. I think it’s knowing when the stream is right.

And just like fishers, some can’t handle the water, some have better luck with their catches, & some can be professionals while others are hobbyists. At least I’m not saying “god speaks through me” like some priests & priestesses do. I’m saying we are all god.

Psychic occurrences are natural, not supernatural. This is a job which benefits society when utilized correctly. There’s training & methodology to consider. Religions attempt to do these things commercially but limit who is considered “touched”. I believe we all are.

Psychics starting out usually expect too much of themselves, wanting to get the right answer all the time. Eventually, we realize it’s a lot like fishing: we can cast our nets or throw our lines into the water and whatever bites we will pick up. We also learn what to throw back.

So why would anyone pay me to ask questions I may or may not know the answer to? Bc if I don’t ask, we won’t know for sure. Usually, I will receive some type of guidance, whatever is intended to be given by me to them at that time. I’m also accurate frequently.

If I was meant to win the lottery, I would know. I’d get a feeling to play & then the numbers would reveal themselves to me. This is why going on game shows is a moot point: unless I have received a message about doing so, it won’t work. “Shouldn’t you have known that?” No.

Usually, the first thing I am asked when I reveal my profession is, “can I get the lotto numbers?” It’s bc there is a general perspective of psychics as being more empowered by their gifts. That isn’t the case nor has it ever been. We get what we get bc we are meant to.
